description:
SEXSCABS.COM
Vintage Boy London Unisex Punk Bondage Trousers, the fly zipper extends all the way from front fly to the ass as this was made for men and women . . . . . Very freaky .
There's a lot of history at 430 King's Road in London's Chelsea district.  'Seditionaries' t-shirts are just a few of the many designs that originated from the various incarnations of the address in the 1970s.
In 1971 the King’s Road location was known as Paradise Garage and future Sex Pistols manager Malcolm McLaren and partner Patrick Casey manned a little rock memorabilia stand located in the back of the store. When the owners of Paradise got evicted McLaren and Casey took over the entire venue and named it Let it Rock expanding their inventory with clothing that was designed by McLaren’s school teacher girlfriend Vivienne Westwood.
In 1972 the shop was re-named Too Fast To Live, To Young to Die and focused on early 1960s rock culture and fashion. This incarnation’s moniker was self-fulfilling prophecy – not even two years later it was no longer living. McLaren and Westwood decided to close up shop because of thievery and threats from the infamous Teddy Boy gang.
In 1974 the shop was gutted, renovated and re-opened under the name SEX. The store specialized in fetish and bondage gear as well as numerous t-shirt designs that caused an uproar by depicting taboo imagery, e.g., gay cowboys, swastikas, etc.
In 1975 McLaren began to manage a band called The Strand that would become the Sex Pistols and Johnny Rotten actually auditioned for the band in the store.  In 1976, the shop was once again re-named to Seditionaries and the inventory reflected the surging popularity of the Sex Pistols who were decked out in designer Seds duds from the get-go. And with Sid Vicious reportedly banking hours as an employee, shoplifting was most likely at an all time low.
Malcolm also sold Seditionaries t-shirts through ads in the Melody Maker. McLaren and Westwood’s relationship eventually deteriorated, they split and closed the Seditionaries store in September of 1980. In 1981 the venue underwent its final make-over and began operating as World’s End.  The location is still in operation and, amazingly, the name has survived two decades and appears to have stuck. The once mom and pop operation is now in the hands of their son, Joe Corre.
To see the Seditionaries shop as it was in the 1970s, watch the documentary film 'Punk Rock Movie'.  This landmark film shot by Don Letts in 1977-1978 provides an amazing glimpse into the London punk rock scene.  In the film, there is a brief tour of the inside of the Seditionaries store with Vivienne Westwood and team working behind the counter and a view of the clothes that were sold there at the time
Towards the late 70's VIVIENNE WESTWOOD licensed some of her graphics from the SEX/Seditionaries period ( 1974 to 1980 ) to BOY. This is why SEDITIONARIES label/labels are present on BOY clothing, or BOY labelled clothing designed by VIVIENNE WESTWOOD.
BOY and BOY LONDON is a clothing label and store founded by Stephane Raynor in 1976. BOY was the punk clothing store to be found halfway down the King's Rd. Raynor briefly lent his hand to opening another famed store, PX, in 1978, where under his guidance the scene surrounding him and his enterprises (led by Visage’s Steve Strange and DJ Rusty Egan) came to be known as the infamous ‘Blitz Kids’ (the original club kids), before returning his full focus to BOY LONDON in the 1980's. The 'BOY' label was used in the 1970's and early 1980's. The word 'LONDON' was added to the store and clothing label in the early 1980's.
(BOY HISTORY) Acme Attractions was a London clothing store on Kings Road, Chelsea, London, that in the early 1970s provided a place for many punk and reggae musicians and scenesters to hang out. Shop assistant and manager Don Letts described Acme Attraction as a place "where the interaction between the different factions became more important than selling merchandise, even though at that age it was a deadly combination". Acme Attractions was inspired by Malcolm McLaren and Vivienne Westwood's Fifties-inspired boutique Let it Rock (revamped in 1972 and renamed Too Fast To Live Too Young To Die), ironically Prior to conceiving BOY, Stephane had been selling 50s clothing to Malcolm Mclaren at his shop ‘Let it Rock’ before opening the his legendary style outlet ‘Acme Attractions’ - which counted punk DJ and filmmaker Don Letts,. In spring 1974, a radical change saw the shop become Sex: selling fetish wear and Westwood's innovative designs. Acme's owner, John Krivine, decided to venture into clothing with Steph Raynor.In 1974, Acme Attractions initially opened as a stall in the antiques market Antiquarius on the King's Road, Chelsea. While it was owned by Krivine and Raynor its public face was Don Letts who says that Acme was selling, "electric-blue zoot suits and jukeboxes, and pumping dub reggae all day long". Acme would actually have to move to the basement, after complaints about Don Letts's pounding dub reggae. By the mid 70s, Acme had quite a scene attracting the likes of The Clash, the Sex Pistols, Chrissie Hynde, Patti Smith, Deborah Harry, Boy George and Bob Marley. Letts remembers that "Marley ... come by because he knew he could get a good draw from the thriving black-market action that also went on in Acme." The scene created by the shop also led to the formation of Generation X, which launched the pop music career of Billy Idol. The Acme accountant, Andrew Czezowski, seeing the potential in the crowd the store attracted, started up The Roxy, the first punk-rock venue in London, so that people could go from the store and have some place to party. Letts was the first house DJ.
Chelsea, a band, formed in August 1976 and were originally managed by John Krivine and Steph Raynor, was in direct competition with Malcolm McLaren's SEX and Sex Pistols.
Seeing the success of punk and how a new market was created for punk related clothing and merchandise John Krevine and Steph Raynor closed Acme Attractions to create Boy London. While Don Letts opened the new store, he soon quit, "It was the bastard child of Acme, created to capitalize on the tabloid punk and although I opened and ran the joint it just weren't my speed. I quit to manage the Slits and headed off on the White Riot tour with The Clash."
Vivienne Westwood licensed designs to Boy, who issued them, some with alterations, over the next eight years. Mr Krivine sold the company in 1984.

description:
Magnet is a brand I can’t seem to find very much information about, but everything I’ve researched has indicated these have been sold out for many years now. Rather lightweight, so despite the aluminum foil vibe, they won’t cook you in the heat. Interestingly, the tag states that these pants are made to distress over time and crack as they age. There’s already a small amount of distressing near the left hand side of the pants, as pictured. The reflective silver color is very vivid in person, making these pants a super unique and flashy statement piece. Reminiscent of the silver pants Iggy Pop wore throughout the 1970s.

RICK OWENS WORKED ON AN ALTERNATE DIFFUSION LINE UNDER THE "SLAB" MONIKER AS WELL AS HIS MAINLINE COLLECTION BACK IN 2004. description:
Really cool asymetric zip jacket from Rick SS14 Vicious. Can be worn multiple ways, has a snap button near the neck that can be snapped and unzip for more of a triangle silhouette, or zip all the way up for a longer column or zip half way with open lapel. In perfect like new condition.
Fit is normal for Rick, I'm 48/50 and it fits me perfectly and I always buy 50 or L in Rick. Fits consistent with other items I have, high arm holes and slim long sleeves give a super elegant silhouette. Sleeves also feature 3 snap buttons on cuffs.

The material is spectacular as only rick can do, like a cotton canvas with a thicker more textured feel and deepest black, this came in a few material iterations and this was the most expensive.

category_3: Rick Owens Long Sleeve T Shirts
description:
•Sizing Reference
I am 5’10-5’11, fairly average build. Weight approx. 170lb. I wear a Size L in tees for a slight oversized and M for a slight slim fit. Size 31-32 waist with a 30-32in inseam length.
•Construction:
On the light to middleweight side with a smooth and silky feel and light luster in the sun.
•Fitting:
It’s a strange one, as the extended arms and cropped, seamless hem adds a contrasting look between arm and body. The drop shoulder is extreme, as the arm hole sits about mid bicep which leads to some extreme lift when arms are raised. This may have been for just me as well, but it’s worth mentioning the shirt seemed to sit a bit behind my shoulder leading to the collar sitting right up against my neck.
•Condition: [7.5/10]
I’ve worn the shirt a handful of times to work, never out with friends or dinner as I was not very comfortable in it. There’s very minuscule stains on the front and back (as pictured) that I have not tried to wash, so they may very well be removable with a light hand wash. Besides the fading on the tag dye, I couldn’t find any other flaws.
•Reason for Sale
As stated before, never felt fully comfortable in the fit. Would do much better in a wardrobe with more layering pieces (or someone more confident than I).
•Offers/Trades
Open to offers, so please do not hesitate!

Killer brown lambskin leather biker jacket from the dark lord himself. It's well known that Rick Owens makes some of the best leather jackets out there, and this jacket is a prime example. The leather is soft and supple and is perfectly distressed - as if you broke it in over decades. The fit is on the slimmer side, but not overly, framing the arms and body just right. Really a beautiful piece.
It's in excellent condition. I had it professionally cleaned recently (paid ~$80), so it's ready for a new home. I will call-out a slight difference in color under each arm (a little darker than the body), however, these are NOT stains and are not noticeable when wearing the jacket. This is part of the patina that's developed over time.

description:
DETAILS
RICK OWENS WORKED ON AN ALTERNATE DIFFUSION LINE UNDER THE "SLAB" MONIKER AS WELL AS HIS MAINLINE COLLECTION BACK IN 2004. IN ADDITION TO THE "SLAB" LINE INTRODUCED IN 2004, RICK OWEN'S HAD ALSO RELEASED A RUNWAY SEASON TITLED "SLAB" IN FALL/WINTER 2001. BEFORE EVOLVING INTO "DRKSHDW" IN 2005 BY PARTNERING WITH MANUFACTURER OLMAR & MIRTA, HIS "SLAB" LINE COVERED A FULL YEAR FROM SS04 TO AW04 AND WAS MAINLY CONSISTED OF HANDMADE GARMENTS PRODUCED IN THE U.S.A. TO ADD A GRUNGE FEEL AND GIVE THE APPEARANCE OF A VINTAGE WEAR & TEAR AESTHETIC, THESE STRAIGHT-FIT JEANS HAVE BEEN HAND-DISTRESSED AND HEAVY WAX-COATED WITH A THICK MUD-WASH COAT. THESE JEANS WERE HANDMADE BY RICK OWEN'S AND HIS SEAMSTRESSES RATHER THAN BEING MASS-PRODUCED IN A FACTORY. EACH PAIR IS UNIQUE.

sub_title: NWT Rick Owens Drkshdw Waxed Detroit Cut

description:
This is, in my opinion, the ultimate iteration of the Gimp hoodie, a staple of the Rick permanent collection. Produced for the mainline in spring-summer 2014 for the 'Vicious' collection, this hoodie features leather detailing that runs up the sides of the main zipper, an extended length hem without elastication, and punchout leather patches as a seasonal detail on the chest. The punchouts are especially cool, since you can use them to add a pop of something else as you layer, or simply have them a textural detail if you wear it over a black tee.
The fabrication is incredible, in a ultra-lux 'FP' fleeced cotton. It feels almost like the ultimate form of the felpa fabric seen on the DRKSHDW version, with more plush and pile that feels extra soft and pleasant on the skin. The body of the hoodie also includes two gigantic front slip pockets, and inside the slip pockets are small velcro pockets so you can put your keys or AirPods in a place where they won't be buried under other stuff, or are otherwise more secured. A highly detail-oriented jacket.
Sized S on the tag, it fits like a Rick 48, good for a true small or a medium looking for a tight fit over a tee. See measurements below for more detail.
This hoodie is in very good condition for its age, stored folded in a closet when it wasn't worn and kept out of harsher elements Los Angeles has to offer. More than happy to answer any questions you might have and feel free to offer away.

RICK OWENS WORKED ON AN ALTERNATE DIFFUSION LINE UNDER THE "SLAB" MONIKER AS WELL AS HIS MAINLINE COLLECTION BACK IN 2004. IN ADDITION TO THE "SLAB" LINE INTRODUCED IN 2004, RICK OWEN'S HAD ALSO RELEASED A RUNWAY SEASON TITLED "SLAB" IN FALL/WINTER 2001. BEFORE EVOLVING INTO "DRKSHDW" IN 2005 BY PARTNERING WITH MANUFACTURER OLMAR & MIRTA, HIS "SLAB" LINE COVERED A FULL YEAR FROM SS04 TO AW04 AND WAS MAINLY CONSISTED OF HANDMADE GARMENTS PRODUCED IN THE U.S.A. TO ADD A GRUNGE FEEL AND GIVE THE APPEARANCE OF A VINTAGE WEAR & TEAR AESTHETIC, THESE STRAIGHT-FIT JEANS HAVE BEEN HAND-DISTRESSED AND HEAVY WAX-COATED WITH A THICK MUD-WASH COAT. designer: Rick Owens x Rick Owens Drkshdw
description: These are the Rick Owens DRKSHDW Made in Japan Selvedge Detroit Jeans in a Black Wax over regular indigo denim color in a Men’s US 34. These jeans have been well loved by me and have some fading as you can see from the get go. The intention of these jeans is to have them fade from the black wax color into a more black indigo denim color over time. These jeans are from a collab with Selfedge and are made in Japan with Japanese selvedge denim. Super comfy jeans that are perfect for a daily driver. I’ve only ever handwashed them once relatively recently and I just don’t really wear them as much anymore ever since I got my Collapse cut pair. These jeans have a rough material feel to them due to the wax, but they will soften over time as the raw black wax fades into the denim underneath. Main flaws are the fading as described, some loose threads (no rips, tears, or seams coming undone though), and some creasing due to wear since these are Mediumweight Selvedge jeans. Feel free to ask any questions! Will be shipped in a USPS Priority Mail Box. Shipping to USA only. Thank you for looking at this listing!
sub_title: Rick Owens DRKSHDW Made in Japan Black Wax Detroit Jeans

designer: Rick Owens x Rick Owens Drkshdw
description: These are brand new and never worn, RARE 2013 denim. I got a bunch of these as many of you know (and see my photos all over Grailed now). I got a million questions about the wax, the oil, etc So I washed and dried one pair to see how they respond. What I got was a crazy muted and softer looking pair. The brown is lighter, the wax and oil are intact but some color was left in the washer. And its insane! Many bought pairs from me and are reselling--buy from a fan, a collector and not a reseller. These are best style of all SLAB denim in my opinion--squared off front pocket with slant underneath--double fronts with crazy distress details--oily, colored threads, well placed shreds, and a killer fit--loose, roomy, straightleg, longer inseam and readymade distressed hems and faux distress. These are staple denim--waxed and oiled with "stains" and wear built in--but the denim will only get better and better. I have a pair of these 10 years old and still are getting better and nowhere close to over. Tagged a 34 and best for a 34-36” waist. 2013 lives on for now. The stash I received is over. Thanks for looking!
sub_title: SLAB 2013 WASHED Waxed and Oiled Double Worker Denim

description:
DETAILS
RICK OWENS WORKED ON AN ALTERNATE DIFFUSION LINE UNDER THE "SLAB" MONIKER AS WELL AS HIS MAINLINE COLLECTION BACK IN 2004. IN ADDITION TO THE "SLAB" LINE INTRODUCED IN 2004, RICK OWEN'S HAD ALSO RELEASED A RUNWAY SEASON TITLED "SLAB" IN FALL/WINTER 2001. BEFORE EVOLVING INTO "DRKSHDW" IN 2005 BY PARTNERING WITH MANUFACTURER OLMAR & MIRTA, HIS "SLAB" LINE COVERED A FULL YEAR FROM SS04 TO AW04 AND WAS MAINLY CONSISTED OF HANDMADE GARMENTS PRODUCED IN THE U.S.A. TO ADD A GRUNGE FEEL AND GIVE THE APPEARANCE OF A VINTAGE WEAR & TEAR AESTHETIC, THESE STRAIGHT-FIT JEANS HAVE BEEN HAND-DISTRESSED AND HEAVY WAX-COATED WITH A THICK MUD-WASH COAT. THE TWO EXTRA FRONT POCKETS THAT GIVE THAT SIGNATURE STAND-OUT LOOK THAT OWEN'S IS USUALLY KNOWN FOR IN HIS WORK. THESE JEANS WERE HANDMADE BY RICK OWEN'S AND HIS SEAMSTRESSES RATHER THAN BEING MASS-PRODUCED IN A FACTORY. EACH PAIR IS UNIQUE.

description:
DETAILS
RICK OWENS WORKED ON AN ALTERNATE DIFFUSION LINE UNDER THE "SLAB" MONIKER AS WELL AS HIS MAINLINE COLLECTION BACK IN 2004. IN ADDITION TO THE "SLAB" LINE INTRODUCED IN 2004, RICK OWEN'S HAD ALSO RELEASED A RUNWAY SEASON TITLED "SLAB" IN FALL/WINTER 2001. BEFORE EVOLVING INTO "DRKSHDW" IN 2005 BY PARTNERING WITH MANUFACTURER OLMAR & MIRTA, HIS "SLAB" LINE COVERED A FULL YEAR FROM SS04 TO AW04 AND WAS MAINLY CONSISTED OF HANDMADE GARMENTS PRODUCED IN THE U.S.A. TO ADD A GRUNGE FEEL AND GIVE THE APPEARANCE OF A VINTAGE WEAR & TEAR AESTHETIC, THESE STRAIGHT-FIT JEANS HAVE BEEN HAND-DISTRESSED AND HEAVY WAX-COATED WITH A THICK MUD-WASH COAT. THE TWO EXTRA FRONT POCKETS THAT GIVE THAT SIGNATURE STAND-OUT LOOK THAT OWEN'S IS USUALLY KNOWN FOR IN HIS WORK. THESE JEANS WERE HANDMADE BY RICK OWEN'S AND HIS SEAMSTRESSES RATHER THAN BEING MASS-PRODUCED IN A FACTORY. EACH PAIR IS UNIQUE.

RICK OWENS WORKED ON AN ALTERNATE DIFFUSION LINE UNDER THE "SLAB" MONIKER AS WELL AS HIS MAINLINE COLLECTION BACK IN 2004. IN ADDITION TO THE "SLAB" LINE INTRODUCED IN 2004, RICK OWEN'S HAD ALSO RELEASED A RUNWAY SEASON TITLED "SLAB" IN FALL/WINTER 2001. BEFORE EVOLVING INTO "DRKSHDW" IN 2005 BY PARTNERING WITH MANUFACTURER OLMAR & MIRTA, HIS "SLAB" LINE COVERED A FULL YEAR FROM SS04 TO AW04 AND WAS MAINLY CONSISTED OF HANDMADE GARMENTS PRODUCED IN THE U.S.A. RICK OWENS WORKED ON AN ALTERNATE DIFFUSION LINE UNDER THE "SLAB" MONIKER AS WELL AS HIS MAINLINE COLLECTION BACK IN 2004. designer: Rick Owens x Rick Owens Drkshdw
description:
SEXSCABS.COM
Recommended 30-31W
Professional Repaired & Reinforced along some of the factory distressing.
Rare archival colourway in a rare defunct Rick color code, he no longer uses in his current collections.
DRKSHDW by Rick Owens started in 2005 following the SS04 & FW04 ‘ SLAB ‘ line and began as a denim label but quickly showed it could offer more than just denim garments. Nonetheless DRKSHDW bottoms are arguably the most coveted on the market and come in a variety of shades and cuts. These Archive Detroit Cuts come in a grey coating over over naval denim, hints of navy can be seen along the hems, waistband, seams, and distressing. These are first ever pair of DRKSHDW denim I owned and are still a popular pair I wear. From my personal closet and a piece I’ve taken to custom repair work over some of the factory distressing and natural wear distressing that started to occur. Navy threading used to sew some of the distressing in place along the leg, thigh and arse seam. I thought the navy stiching would add to the hints of navy along the waistband, seams, and hems.
Private Appointments & trades available in house located in Los Angeles, CA
@SEXSCABSINC
Please be aware that majority of all garments are vintage or second-hand and have been previously worn. Each item may show varying degrees of wear and tear. Returns or exchanges are not accepted at this time. All sales are final. We are not responsible for any garments once they are shipped out.

RICK OWENS WORKED ON AN ALTERNATE DIFFUSION LINE UNDER THE "SLAB" MONIKER AS WELL AS HIS MAINLINE COLLECTION BACK IN 2004. description:
RP20F2890-LDEP
Performa 2020 Ramones
sz 40 (fits 7 with a thin insole or 7.5 without)
Very good condition 8.5-9/10
I wore these with a superfeet black insole at all times, so I didn't leave a print in the footbed and there is zero odor. Just some dust inside.
Vibramed as soon as I got them so the original sole would have as little heel drag as possible.
The vibram sole has come loose on one small part but a cobbler can fix this extremely easily.
I can even recommend the one I used (you can ship them).
When the vibram sole wears away, a new one can be slapped right on. These will last forever as long as the upper is kept as perfect as it is now.
if you're curious about the vibram sole, look up "Rick Owens Heeldrag" on Youtube and you'll see what I mean. Superior to heel taps and the best possible compromise between protecting the shoe and keeping the original look.
Original laces replaced with even longer custom rick laces. Off-white/cream and regular white custom rick laces included. They look ridiculously good.
Original box was seized by customs, recently removed the customs label off of it but box still looks bad.
Any questions, ask away.

description:
This item is Pre-owned! Its condition is shown in the photos and described below. Please, check all the photos and description very carefully before message me and ask ALL the questions that bother you strictly before or making a payment/offer! ALL MY ITEMS ARE 100% AUTHENTIC, if you think differently, please DON’T WASTE MY TIME! You can FOLLOW ME in order not to miss my regular updates and price drops in future. Also check my other listings, you can find a big variety of rare and unique archival items of different types and styles in my store, both vintage and from the latest collections. If you choose more than one item in my store, I can combine them and send as one parcel. In this case, I will make a discount on your order and you will greatly save on shipping. By making me an offer or a payment, you confirm that you have carefully read and agree with the condition of the item and my store’s policy of work, described below. Thank you!
DESCRIPTION:
Rare Vintage Stone Island Heavy Knit Beige / Black 1/3 Zip Cotton Sweater with Embroidered Square Patch Badge
from Spring / Summer 2005 Collection
Art. 421551a2/737
Lampo zip
Made in Italy of 100% Cotton
Tag size EU 52-54 / US L, but better check the measurements:
Pit to pit - 54 cm
Waist - 54 cm
Hem - 55.5 cm
Shoulder seams are absent
Sleeve to armpit - 47 cm
Sleeve to shoulder - 74 cm
Total (Back) length - 62 cm
All measurements were made lying flat.
Please allow for possible actual measurement deviation from stated + -0.5 cm (+ -0.2 in). In order to exclude the possibility of buying clothes of the wrong size, please avoid purchasing if, based on measurements, this lot is smaller than similar item with correct fit that you already have.
Normal used condition, natural for this fabric. Minimal pills and a small group of spots in the front bottom part, check the photos. So as the color of spots is similar to the sweater color, they are not visible a lot on body.
PAYMENT:
IMPORTANT! If my price for this item is not much higher than you are ready to pay for it, you can make me a reasonable offer and maybe we can make a deal. Everybody wants the best price on items they are interested in, but, please, avoid ridiculously low offers, such as half price etc. I am as much interested in selling this item as you are in buying it, so if I were ready to cut the price significantly, for example, in a half, I would have already done it by myself. Hope for your understanding. Sometimes, after re-listing my ads, the shipping cost for some reason is no longer displayed in the ad, but please note that shipping cost is not included in the price indicated for the item. So, please remember to include shipping cost into your offer! If you've already completed the payment, made me a discussed beforehand price offer or accepted mine offer, please provide me with your contact phone number to reach the quickest possible shipment of your parcel, as my local postal service requires me to sign it to make a shipment.
IF YOU HAVE ANY QUESTIONS OR NEED ANY ADDITIONAL INFORMATION OR PHOTOS OF THIS ITEM - PLEASE, ASK ALL THE QUESTIONS THAT BOTHER YOU BEFORE MAKING A PAYMENT OR OFFER AND I WILL PROVIDE YOU WITH ANY PHOTOS, MEASUREMENTS, COMPLETE AND DETAILED DESCRIPTION OF THE ITEM.
RETURNS OR REFUNDS:
Due to the whole list of extra taxes and fees inside of my country (in addition to Grailed and PP fees), possible additional taxes in some receiving countries (like Sweden) and big shipping terms and cost, returns or refunds are absolutely not profitable and convenient to none of us. Also, I want you to get definitely the item you need and expect. Therefore, before sending, I always carefully check the condition of the item you are interested in once again to exclude the possibility of presence of any defects, not indicated in the description or in the photos. But please ask for ANY measurements, additional photos, information about the item, shipping terms and cost, postal services, customs control procedure or ANY other questions that bother you STRICTLY BEFORE making a payment or price offer! I am always happy to answer all your questions as soon as possible.
SHIPPING:
I provide worldwide shipping via "UkrPoshta" (registered air delivery). Your parcel will be shipped in the day the payment is received or the next day. In case of holidays or other extraordinary circumstances, it will be shipped not later than in 2 business days since receiving a payment.
IMPORTANT! In order to avoid delays in shipment, please provide me with your contact phone number after payment has been completed. My local postal service requires me to sign it to make a shipment. Thanks in advance!
Current shipping terms:
US, UK, Europe - 10-16 days, in rare cases can increase up to 21 days.
Canada, New Zealand - 21-30 days, in rare cases can increase up to 40 days.
Currently not shipping to Australia, but ask for details/updates.
Asia - 15-21 days, in rare cases can increase up to 31 days.
Delivery terms to other countries are very diverse, ask all the details in messages.
If fast delivery is your main priority and you are ready to compensate its cost, I can send the package via DHL (at your expense) and it will take two days to a week (depending on your location) for the package to reach your house, but in my country, for some reason, their services are unreasonably expensive, often even more expensive, than the item itself.
IMPORTANT! I'm always very worried about the parcels I send, so I always track them and inform my customers about their location until they get the parcel. I always do everything in my power to ensure that the customer gets the parcel without any problems, but you must understand that I don't personally provide the delivery, therefore, I cannot be responsible for minor delays. Also I always indicate my parcels as a gift with 40$ equivalent or lower value in the customs declaration when sending them to save your money on taxes. If you are familiar with the way your local postal and custom services work and you know how to save extra money on shipping or customs, I'm always ready to help you with that.
Wish you a good shopping and see you in my store! Best wishes, Wuzzym!

This piece is fucking magnificent, wish the pictures were a bit better but they are good enough to get the jist. Ok so:

2. This shirt is made from “Seda Francesca” which is “Francesca Silk”. I cant find info online about what that means, other than that yes it is silk and that other companies use it. Its heavier than all silk Ive felt, maybe its a blend? I dont know but its nice
3. The detailing is fantastic. The cuts of the pockets. The collar. The fabric. The soft lavender colour of the front pattern.
Overall, its just an amazing shirt. Seems like a miami vice drug dealer vibe, or just a really kind old man kind if vibe.
Tagged size 46 - Id say it fits a Large. Check measurements
Comes as shown

Item Description:
(Our Double Match Bowling shirt takes on a classic silhouette, the bowling shirt. Seen perfected by Prada, the double match look takes 2 apperances and combines them into one shirt. On one side, you will find a simple lined graphic laying on a beige background. On the other side, you have a very unique and interesting graphic. In order to juxtapose the plain, we have an intricate design on the opposite side of Julius Caesar over an abstract canvas. This shirt is printed on a high quality 100% Polyester blank, finished with simple hemming, lapel collar and button closure.)
Item Details:
Material: 100% Polyester
Wear - Ability: Unisex for men and women
Style: Button Up Hawaiian shirt
Collar type: lapel
sleeve length: short sleeve

*We also offer a couple more expedited services (Dhl, USPS, etc.)
(Please allow up to 7 processing days post purchase, you will get a tracking number within 2 days of purchase.)
Returns 📦: WE DO NOT OFFER RETURNS. A STRICT NO REFUND POLICY.
Where do our items come from?:
China. And among various worldwide factories, including varying factories in the United States, Canada and Others. We are a manufacturer and product sourcing and distributing team. Also known as Drop-Shipping. We offer a premium supply and excellent quality, as well as a multitude of our own designs.
Social Media 📲
Instagram: PeaceMustBeClo
Website: PeaceMustBe.com
Our push for a sustainable environment:
-Our packaging is biodegradable and does not impact our environment negatively
-We do not dispose of unnecessary packaging and materials
-We do not serve authentic leathers and furs, in respect of the welfare of animals
-We are a carbon neutral shipping service, aiming to provide 10% of shares to Charity to combat humanity
